http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Women-in-distress-can-now-dial-%E2%80%98182%E2%80%99/article14026319.ece

Railway Protection Force (RPF), Renigunta, on Thursday organised an awareness programme at Sri Padmavathi Mahila Viswa Vidyalayam (SPMVV) on Thursday on ‘Dial 182’, a security helpline system launched by the Indian Railways.The system functions through the security controls of the RPF, providing round-the-clock assistance to passengers across the country, especially safety cover for women in distress.The new security helpline number, ‘182’, came into operation in all divisions of the SCR. “Whenever the control room receives a call in distress, an alert with details of the train and the nature of the complaint will be immediately relayed to the train escort personnel ,” said M.M. Khan, RPF Commandant, Guntakal.